summaries.short: Ben and Rachel's platonic friendship is tested; Cam scores a plum location for a CRISP photo shoot; Rene collects on a debt.
summaries.full: Ben's platonic friendship with Rachel is tested. Meanwhile, Kapo stresses about speaking from the heart in his best-man speech; Cam charms Lulu's dad to secure the perfect location (and an unlikely model) for CRISP's new 'lookbook' photo shoot; Rene seeks to collect on a debt to cover the costs of Rasta Monsta's expanding business (and to buy bling for Debbie).

summaries.full: After Nancy puts the kibosh on getting CRISP into a large midwestern retailer, Ben and Cam take matters into their own hands to charm its young out-of-town buyers. summaries.full: Fashion rep Nancy lands CRISP a promising but unpaid gig. Rachel bestows a lavish gift on Ben after learning that he and Julie may be parting ways. summaries.full: Ben senses a conflict of interest when Nancy sets CRISP up with a manufacturer named Yosi. The Feds catch up with Kapo; Lulu warns Cam against selling out; and Rasta Monsta incites the ire of the East Flatbush Caribbean League.
